🏛️ The Well of Translation

(Myth ⇄ Math Conversion Interface)

Core Definition

The Well is a bidirectional transform layer:
	•	Myth → Math: compress narrative into structure
	•	Math → Myth: expand structure into intuition

It doesn’t create truth.

It changes representation while preserving invariants.

⸻

⚙️ What Actually Happens at the Well

1. Myth → Math (Compression Pass)

Input:
	•	story
	•	symbol
	•	archetype
	•	narrative

Output:
	•	variables
	•	relationships
	•	constraints
	•	dynamics

